<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263267>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 4. Wings of Metalimnobia (Metalimnobia). 1: M. (M.) bifasciata; 2: M. (M.) bifasciata, variation of wing shape; 3: M. (M.) quadrimaculata; 4: M. (M.) zetterstedti. Abbreviation: d, discal cell." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263267/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263270>
    dc:description "FIGURES 15 – 16. Holotype of Metalimnobia (Metalimnobia) channpayna sp. nov. 15: General view; 16: Male genitalia, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263270/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.263268>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6 – 11. Male genitalia of Metalimnobia (Metalimnobia), dorsal view. 6: M. (M.) bifasciata; 7: M. (M.) quadrimaculata; 8: Aedeagus of M. (M.) quadrimaculata; 9: Gonocoxite with gonostyles of M. (M.) quadrimaculata; 10: M. (M.) quadrinotata; 11: M. (M.) zetterstedti. Abbreviations: gonx, gonocoxite; i gonst, inner gonostylus; o gonst, outer gonostylus; p, penis; pm, paramere; tg 9, ninth tergite; vm l, ventro-mesal lobe of gonocoxite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/263268/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

